      <hedline>
        <hl1>A Screenful of Windows</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Letter by Michael Meisels responds to May 25 Q&amp;&amp;A column; says Windows operating system has a built-in shortcut to close a window and all its parent windows</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>The Q &amp; A column of May 25 (''Quick Ways to Close a Screenful of Windows'') suggested a shareware program named Closer to close all open windows. Windows has a built-in shortcut to close a window and all its parent windows simultaneously. Hold down the shift key while closing the window.</p>
        <p>MICHAEL MEISELS  Far Rockaway, Queens</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
